title: Ram Dass - One Man's Journey to the East 1969
description:
Live Recording - Two Cassettes
Ram Dass talks about his personal journey - from being a professor at Harvard, through a period of psychedelics use, to finding his guru in India, as well as the continuing changes in his life.

Note: The inherent difficulties of live recordings and the age of some of the recordings can cause variations in the sound quality.

RAM DASS, the former Richard Alpert, has over the last 25 years become a true embodiment of a spiritual seeker. As a psychologist and spiritual teacher, he has authored numerous books including "Be Here Now" and "Grist for the Mill."
